Layout Options JSON.description: You can use layout options to configure the layout algorithm. A list of all options and further details of their exact effects is available in ELK's documentation.

Default padding.description: Padding between the bounding box of the selected elements, and the box the script creates

Palette folder.description: The path to the folder where you store the Excalidraw Palettes

Light-gray.description: Base light-gray used for mixing with the accent color to generate the palette light-gray

Dark-gray.description: Base dark-gray used for mixing with the accent color to generate the palette dark-gray

Step size.description: Step size in percentage for making the color darker

Background Color.description: Default background color of the 'shadow' object. Any valid html css color value

Fill Style.description: Default fill style of the 'shadow' object.

Inherit fill stroke width.description: This will impact the densness of the hachure or cross-hatch fill. Use the stroke width of the line object for which the shadow is created. If set to false, the script will use a stroke width of 2.

Group 'shadow' with original.description: If the toggle is on then the shadow object that is created will be grouped with the unclosed original object.

Point density.description: A freedraw object has many points. Converting freedraw to a line with too many points will result in an impractical object that is hard to edit. This setting sepcifies how many points from freedraw should be averaged to form a point on the line

Border color.description: Any legal HTML color (#000000, rgb, color-name, etc.). Set to 'transparent' for transparent color.

Background color.description: Background color of the sticky note. Set to 'transparent' for transparent color.

Background fill style.description: Fill style of the sticky note

Max sticky note width.description: Maximum width of new sticky note. If text is longer, it will be wrapped

Sticky note width.description: Preferred width of the sticky note. Set to 0 if unset.

Sticky note height.description: Preferred height of the sticky note. Set to 0 if unset.

Rows per column.description: If multiple text elements are converted to sticky notes in one step, how many rows before a next column is created. Only effective if fixed width & height are given. 0 for unset.

Open link in active pane.description: Open the link in the current active pane (on) or a new pane (off).

Line points.description: Number of line points between start and end

Fix width.description: The object around the text should have fix width to fit the wrapped text

Pen folder.description: The path to the folder where you store the perfect freehand options

MindMap Format.description: This is prepared for the namespace of MindMap Format and does not need to be modified

curve length.description: The length of the curve part in the mind map line

length between element and line.description: The distance between the tail of the connection and the connecting elements of the mind map

Default padding.description: Padding between the bounding box of the selected elements, and the box the script creates

Line points.description: Number of line points between start and end

Gap.description: The value of the gap between the connection line and the element, which must be greater than 0. If you want the connector to be next to the element, set it to 1.
